content.text:
{
  "message": "Issue updated successfully",
  "issue": {
    "id": "27409",
    "key": "DEV-5786",
    "summary": "Implement Subscription Limit Enforcement",
    "url": "https://procurementsciences.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/27409",
    "description": "## User Story\nAs a system, I need to enforce user limits based on subscription tiers so that tenants cannot exceed their allowed user count.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Define subscription tiers and user limits in configuration\n- [ ] Validate user count before allowing new user creation\n- [ ] Display current user count vs limit in admin panel\n- [ ] Prevent user creation when limit would be exceeded\n- [ ] Clear error messages when limits are reached\n- [ ] Grace period handling for temporary overages (if applicable)\n\n## Technical Notes\n- Create subscription service to manage tier information\n- Integrate with billing/subscription system if available\n- Add user count tracking and validation middleware\n- Consider caching for performance optimization\n\n## Questions to Resolve\n- What are the specific subscription tiers and limits?\n- How should grace periods be handled?\n- Integration points with billing system?",
